.TH LIGMATOOL\-2.0 1 "Version @LIGMA_VERSION@" "LIGMA Manual Pages"

.SH NAME
ligmatool\-2.0 - script to perform various LIGMAy functions


.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ligmatool\-2.0
[\-\-prefix\fI[=DIR]\fP] [\-\-exec\-prefix\fI[=DIR]\fP] [\-\-version]
[\-\-help] [\-\-quiet] [\-\-silent] [\-n] [\-\-just-print] [\-\-dry-run]
[\-\-recon] [\-\-msvc-syntax]
[\-\-bindir] [\-\-sbindir] [\-\-libexecdir] [\-\-datadir]
[\-\-sysconfdir] [\-\-sharedstatedir] [\-\-localstatedir] [-\-libdir]
[\-\-infodir] [\-\-mandir] [\-\-includedir] [\-\-ligmaplugindir]
[\-\-ligmadatadir] [\-\-libs] [\-\-libs-noui] [\-\-cflags] [\-\-cflags-noi]
[\-\-build \fIplug\-in.c\fP]
[\-\-build\-strip \fIplug\-in.c\fP] [\-\-install \fIplug\-in.c\fP]
[\-\-install-strip \fIplug\-in.c\fP] [\-\-install-admin \fIplug-in.c\fP] 
[\-\-install\-bin \fIplug\-in\fP]
[\-\-install\-admin\-strip \fIplug-in.c\fP]
[\-\-install\-bin\-strip \fIplug\-in\fP]
[\-\-\install\-admin\-bin \fIplug\-in\fP]
[\-\-install\-script \fIscript.scm\fP] 
[\-\-\install\-admin\-script \fIscript.scm\fP]
[\-\-uninstall\-bin \fIplug\-in\fP] [\-\-uninstall\-admin\-bin \fIplug\-in\fP]
[\-\-uninstall\-script \fIscript.scm\fP]
[\-\-uninstall\-admin\-script \fIscript.scm\fP]


.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\fIligmatool\-2.0\fP is a tool that can, among other things, build
plug-ins or scripts and install them if they are distributed in one
source file.
.PP
\fIligmatool\-2.0\fP can also be used by programs that need to know what
libraries and include-paths \fILIGMA\fP was compiled with. \fIligmatool\-2.0\fP
uses \fIpkg-config\fP for this task. For use in Makefiles, it is recommended
that you use \fIpkg-config\fP directly instead of calling \fIligmatool\-2.0\fP.


.SH OPTIONS
\fIligmatool\-2.0\fP accepts the following options:
.TP 8
.B  \-\-version
Print the currently installed version of \fILIGMA\fP on the standard output.
.TP 8
.B \-\-help
Print out the help blurb, showing commonly used commandline options.
.TP 8
.B \-\-quiet
Run quietly without echoing any of the build commands.
.TP 8
.B \-\-silent
Run silently without echoing any of the build commands. Same as \-\-quiet.
.TP 8
.B \-n
Test mode. Print the commands but don't actually execute them. Useful for
making dry runs for testing.
.TP 8
.B \-\-just-print
Test mode. Print the commands but don't actually execute them. Same as \-n.
.TP 8
.B \-\-dry-run
Test mode. Print the commands but don't actually execute them. Same as \-n.
.TP 8
.B \-\-recon
Test mode. Print the commands but don't actually execute them. Same as \-n.
.TP 8
.B \-\-msvc-syntax
Useful on Windows. Outputs the compiler and linker flags in the syntax
used by Microsoft's toolchain. Passed to the pkg-config command that
does most of \fIligmatool\-2.0\fP's work.
.TP 8
.B \-\-bindir
Outputs the bindir used to install the \fILIGMA\fP.
.TP 8
.B \-\-sbindir
Outputs the sbindir used to install the \fILIGMA\fP.
.TP 8
.B \-\-libexecdir
Outputs the libexecdir used to install the \fILIGMA\fP.
.TP 8
.B \-\-datadir
Outputs the datadir used to install the \fILIGMA\fP.
.TP 8
.B \-\-sysconfdir
Outputs the sysconfdir used to install the \fILIGMA\fP.
.TP 8
.B \-\-sharedstatedir
Outputs the sharedstatedir used to install the \fILIGMA\fP.
.TP 8
.B \-\-localstatedir
Outputs the localstatedir used to install the \fILIGMA\fP.
.TP 8
.B \-\-libdir
Outputs the libdir used to install the \fILIGMA\fP.
.TP 8
.B \-\-infodir
Outputs the infodir used to install the \fILIGMA\fP.
.TP 8
.B \-\-mandir
Outputs the mandir used to install the \fILIGMA\fP.
.TP 8
.B \-\-includedir
Outputs the includedir used to install the \fILIGMA\fP.
.TP 8
.B \-\-ligmadatadir
Outputs the actual directory where the \fILIGMA\fP data files were installed.
.TP 8
.B \-\-ligmaplugindir
Outputs the actual directory where the \fILIGMA\fP plug-ins were installed.
.TP 8
.B  \-\-build \fIplug-in.c\fP
Compile and link \fIplug-in.c\fP into a \fILIGMA\fP plug-in.
.TP 8
.B  \-\-build\-strip \fIplug-in.c\fP
Compile,link, and strip \fIplug-in.c\fP into a \fILIGMA\fP plug-in.
.TP 8
.B  \-\-install \fIplug-in.c\fP
Compile, link, and install \fIplug-in.c\fP into the user's personal
\fILIGMA\fP plug-in directory (@manpage_ligmadir@/plug-ins)
.TP 8
.B  \-\-install\-strip \fIplug-in.c\fP
Compile, link,strip, and install \fIplug-in.c\fP into the user's
personal \fILIGMA\fP
plug-in directory (@manpage_ligmadir@/plug-ins)
.TP 8
.B  \-\-install\-admin \fIplug-in.c\fP
Compile, link, and install \fIplug-in.c\fP into the system-wide \fILIGMA\fP
plug-in directory (@ligmaplugindir@/plug-ins)
.TP 8
.B  \-\-install\-bin \fIplug-in\fP
Install \fIplug-in\fP into the user's personal \fILIGMA\fP
plug-in directory (@manpage_ligmadir@/plug-ins)
.TP 8
.B  \-\-install\-admin\-bin \fIplug-in\fP
Install \fIplug-in\fP into the system-wide \fILIGMA\fP
plug-in directory (@ligmaplugindir@/plug-ins)
.TP 8
.B  \-\-install\-bin\-strip \fIplug-in\fP
Install stripped \fIplug-in\fP into the user's personal \fILIGMA\fP
plug-in directory (@manpage_ligmadir@/plug-ins)
.TP 8
.B  \-\-install\-admin\-bin\-strip \fIplug-in\fP
Install stripped \fIplug-in\fP into the system-wide \fILIGMA\fP
plug-in directory (@ligmaplugindir@/plug-ins)
.TP 8
.B  \-\-install\-script \fIscript.scm\fP
Install \fIscript.scm\fP into the user's personal \fILIGMA\fP
script directory (@manpage_ligmadir@/scripts)
.TP 8
.B  \-\-install\-admin\-script \fIscript.scm\fP
Install \fIscript.scm\fP into the system-wide \fILIGMA\fP
script directory (@ligmadatadir@/scripts)
.TP 8
.B  \-\-uninstall\-bin \fIplug-in\fP
Uninstall \fIplug-in\fP from the user's personal \fILIGMA\fP
plug-in directory (@manpage_ligmadir@/plug-ins)
.TP 8
.B  \-\-uninstall\-admin\-bin \fIplug-in\fP
Uninstall \fIplug-in\fP from the system-wide \fILIGMA\fP
plug-in directory (@ligmaplugindir@/plug-ins)
.TP 8
.B  \-\-uninstall\-script \fIscript.scm\fP
Uninstall \fIscript.scm\fP from the user's personal \fILIGMA\fP
script directory (@manpage_ligmadir@/scripts)
.TP 8
.B  \-\-uninstall\-admin\-script \fIscript.scm\fP
Uninstall \fIscript.scm\fP from the system-wide \fILIGMA\fP
script directory (@ligmadatadir@/scripts)
.TP 8
.B  \-\-libs
Print the linker flags that are necessary to link a \fILIGMA\fP plug-in.
.TP 8
.B \-\-libs-noui
Print the linker flags that are necessary to link a \fILIGMA\fP plug-in, for
plug-ins that do not require the GTK libraries.
.TP 8
.B  \-\-cflags
Print the compiler flags that are necessary to compile a \fILIGMA\fP plug-in.
.TP 8
.B \-\-clags-noui
Print the compiler flags that are necessary to compile a \fILIGMA\fP plug-in
for plug-ins that do not require the GTK libraries.
.TP 8
.B  \-\-prefix=PREFIX
If specified, use PREFIX instead of the installation prefix that \fILIGMA\fP
was built with when computing the output for the \-\-cflags and
\-\-libs options. This option is also used for the exec prefix
if \-\-exec\-prefix was not specified. This option must be specified
before any \-\-libs or \-\-cflags options.
.TP 8
.B  \-\-exec\-prefix=PREFIX
If specified, use PREFIX instead of the installation exec prefix that
\fILIGMA\fP was built with when computing the output for the \-\-cflags
and \-\-libs options. This option must be specified before any
\-\-libs or \-\-cflags options.


.SH ENVIRONMENT
.PP
.TP 8
.B CC
to get the name of the desired C compiler.
.TP 8
.B CFLAGS
to get the preferred flags to pass to the C compiler for plug-in building.
.TP 8
.B LDFLAGS
to get the preferred flags for passing to the linker.
.TP 8
.B LIBS
for passing extra libs that may be needed in the build process. For example,
LIBS=-lintl .
.TP 8
.B PKG_CONFIG
to get the location of the \fIpkg-config\fP program that is used to determine
details about your glib, pango, gtk and ligma installation.


